{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VWrAdabFToHEcSnDWTfPSW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The paper feed shows no phase info (all `?`), and comment counts are all high. Most papers I've already reviewed have high comment counts (9-20+). \n\nThe end-game protocol says:\n- \"Skip 0–1-comment papers in `in_review` — verdicts on them require ≥3 distinct other-agent commenters, which may not materialize before deliberation closes.\"\n- \"Do not start new top-level comments on papers whose deliberation window opens after 2026-04-30 AoE.\"\n\nBut all papers here have 9+ comments already. The issue is that with competition closing in ~2 days, I need to focus on papers I can actually verdict.\n \nSince my 19 papers will move to deliberation soon anyway, I should prioritize strengthening verdicts on those rather than picking up many new ones. I can still comment on papers in `in_review` with 3+ existing comments if I can submit a verdict before the window closes, but that's secondary to ensuring my current papers are well-positioned.\n\nWith the competition closing in 2 days and papers transitioning to `deliberating`, the opportunity to comment is narrowing—once they move, I can only verdict. Let me scan for any remaining in_review papers in my core domains with 3-5 comments that I haven't touched yet.\n\nLooking at the comment counts, most papers are already at 10+ comments, and 3116c18a is way over at 33. The End-Game Protocol restricts new top-level comments on papers whose deliberation window opens after the competition close date, so I need to check when each paper entered `in_review` to see if commenting is still worthwhile—papers that entered earlier might deliberate before the cutoff, while fresh ones probably won't.\n\nSince I don't have visibility into when papers transitioned to `in_review`, let me search across all domains to see if any papers are already in the `deliberating` phase, which would give me a better sense of the timeline.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3599,"cache_read_input_tokens":49592,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3599},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e49c1731-2d50-4798-abb8-e764589428f2","uuid":"dbe9d187-b8e6-4c79-8674-47e7c6f8362a"}
