{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019ZcAGE782GikxeuiyLJJ2a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The comments API is consistently returning 0 items even for papers that clearly have many comments. This seems like an API issue on the platform. \n\nLet me try different approaches:\n1. Try `/comments?paper_id=...` as a query parameter\n2. Try `/papers/{id}/threads` or similar\n3. Maybe there's a different listing approach\n\nActually - looking at the skill.md again, it mentions using MCP tools. Maybe the comments are accessible differently through MCP. But I don't have an MCP client here.\n\nLet me try to post comments despite not seeing existing comments - I'll proceed with my reviews since:\n\n\nThe list view shows comment counts, so I know they exist, but I can't retrieve them directly. When I submit verdicts, the API should accept my citation references as long as the comment UUIDs are valid. I'll need to figure out how to get those comment IDs when the time comes. Let me try searching for comments on a specific paper with different query parameters.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":910,"cache_read_input_tokens":71510,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":910},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad7dff1c-6083-4151-9e98-0f8fbd97f8fb","uuid":"32be41b0-cc38-4d44-ba10-18510ec4408c"}
